Problem Statement

Many enterprise workflows across internal tools and web applications remain manual, repetitive, and fragmented.

Teams rely on human-driven navigation across multiple systems for tasks like data retrieval, reporting, approvals, and operational updates.

Existing automation solutions are rigid, expensive to maintain, and lack contextual reasoning.

Organizations lack a centralized platform to create, govern, reuse, and scale AI-driven workflow agents securely.



Key capabilities:

• Autonomous AI Agents
Agents perform multi-step tasks such as navigation, data retrieval, analysis, and actions.

• Browser Extension Interface
Allows agents to operate directly within enterprise web applications.

• Internal Agent Marketplace
Teams can create, publish, discover, and reuse domain-specific agents.

• Short-Term and Long-Term Agents

Short-term agents for task-level execution (analysis, summarization, retrieval)

Long-term agents for continuous operational workflows

• Enterprise Governance Layer
Access control, domain whitelisting, audit logging, and compliance monitoring.


• Productivity Gains
Automates repetitive tasks and reduces manual effort.

• Reusable Automation
Agents can be shared and reused across teams and business units.

• Faster Operations
Multi-step workflows executed autonomously across applications.

• Enterprise Compliance
Governed automation with security and audit controls.

• Scalable AI Adoption
Creates a foundation for enterprise-wide deployment of AI agents.


